@node "Limitations" "Limitations"

   Help to keep the concept of shareware alive!

   Gotcha is shareware, to make it easier for you to decide where you want
   to register or not the unregistered version will open a little window
   each time you start it to remind you that you haven't registered.

   In addition to that the unregistered version has limits on how many calls
   it can make (outgoing and incomming). After two connections Gotcha
   will sooner or later quit.

   Registered users will receive a personalized keyfile which will remove
   the "remind requester" and the connection limits. This keyfile will work
   with all future versions of Gotcha.


   How to become a registered user:

   Fill out the @{"Registration Form" link "Registration_Form" 0}, print it out, sign it and send it
   along with the registration fee to me.

   The Keyfile will be sent to your email address or on disk to your
   postal address (as you like).
@endnode

